# =============================================================================
# studio-r2-sidecart demo — example environment file
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to `demos/studio-r2-sidecart/.env` and fill in real values.
# `.env` is gitignored everywhere in this repo (see top-level .gitignore), so
# the secrets you put here never leave your machine.
#
# Lookup order (first non-blank wins, per key):
#   1. Process environment (`export VECTORS_R2_BUCKET=…`)
#   2. JVM system property (`-DVECTORS_R2_BUCKET=…`)
#   3. This `.env` file
#
# The Gradle `runSeed` task sets `-Ddotenv.directory=<this demo's projectDir>`,
# so this `.env` is the one consulted when you run:
#
#   ./gradlew :demos:studio-r2-sidecart:runSeed --args="--sidecart=H2"
#
# Both the seeder CLI and the live integration test (`BulkIngestorR2IT`) read
# from this file. The IT self-skips when the R2 keys are blank, so it is safe
# to leave the file partially populated during development.
# =============================================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible) — required for `runSeed` and BulkIngestorR2IT
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The endpoint URL is derived from VECTORS_R2_ACCOUNT_ID by default, in the
# form `https://<account-id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com`. Set VECTORS_R2_ENDPOINT
# explicitly only if you need a jurisdiction-specific endpoint such as
# `.eu.r2.cloudflarestorage.com`.
#
# Region is ignored by R2 but the AWS SDK requires *some* value; `auto` is the
# Cloudflare-recommended placeholder.
#
# How to obtain these:
#   1. Cloudflare dashboard → R2 → Manage R2 API Tokens → "Create API Token".
#   2. Scope the token to the bucket below with Read & Write permissions.
#   3. Copy the Access Key ID and Secret Access Key shown once on token
#      creation (they are not retrievable later).

VECTORS_R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
VECTORS_R2_BUCKET=
VECTORS_R2_ACCESS_KEY=
VECTORS_R2_SECRET_KEY=
# VECTORS_R2_ENDPOINT=https://<account-id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
# VECTORS_R2_REGION=auto


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare D1 — required only for `runSeed --sidecart=D1`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When `--sidecart=H2` (the default sidecart kind in most examples) the demo
# writes to a local H2 file at `./build/sidecart.mv.db` and these keys can stay
# blank. They are only consulted when `--sidecart=D1` is passed on the CLI.
#
# How to obtain these:
#   1. `npx wrangler d1 create <db-name>` (or via the Cloudflare dashboard) and
#      copy the printed `database_id` into VECTORS_D1_DATABASE_ID below.
#   2. Cloudflare dashboard → My Profile → API Tokens → "Create Token" →
#      "Custom token" → grant `Account / D1 / Edit` on the same account, then
#      copy the token into VECTORS_CF_API_TOKEN below.
#
# VECTORS_CF_ACCOUNT_ID falls back to VECTORS_R2_ACCOUNT_ID when blank, so
# users with a single Cloudflare account only need to fill it in once above.

# VECTORS_CF_ACCOUNT_ID=
VECTORS_CF_API_TOKEN=
VECTORS_D1_DATABASE_ID=
